Henceforth implement within the timeline as scheduled in the AIP thru an  updated preparation of technical documents for the projects on the part of the MEO, and effective monitoring on the part of the MPDC, consistent with  the mandated responsibility of LGU officials, as embodied in the Joint DBM-DILG Memorandum Circular 2017-1;
Require the Budget Officer and Accountant to revert the unutilized balances of implemented or completed PPAs to the Unappropriated Surplus and/or recommend for its reappropriation  for other priority  PPAs.
Appoint a permanent official that will head the MPDC apart from the MEO so that both offices may be able to exercise its mandated functions more effectively.

We recommended that management:
a) Fast track the implementation of the PPAs consistent with the MOAs for the benefit of the targeted constituents;
b) Return to the Source Agency the balance of unutilized fund for completed projects in accordance with COA Circular No. 94-013 to enable the National government to re-appropriate the funds to other priority programs.

We recommended that the LCE through the Municipal Assessor:
take appropriate steps in order to attain 100% revision of all Tax Declarations of all RPUs in the municipality and submit the updated records to the Provincial Assessor as pre-requisite to the next General Revision and;
coordinate with the Provincial Assessor so that the 4th General Revision of Assessments and Property Classification be made as early as possible.

We recommended that the LCE;
Require the Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Accountant to adhere strictly to  the provisions of Section 322 of RA 7160. Unobligated appropriations for Personel Services and MOOE should be reverted to the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund at every end of the year and should not be made available for expenditure except by subsequent enactment.
b) Require also the reversion to the unappropriated surplus, the CY 2017 unexpended MOOE balance of P2,443,700.75 which was previously classified as continuing appropriation, to the unappropriated surplus in the General Fund.

We recommended that management:
Implement immediately the unimplemented projects under the 20% DF for the current and prior years;
Henceforth, implement within the timeline as scheduled in the agency Annual Investment Program, all development projects consistent with the general policy of the government and mandated responsibility of LGU officials, as embodied in the Joint DBM-DILG Memorandum Circular 2011-1 and;
Require the Budget Officer and Accountant to revert the unutilized balances of implemented or completed PPAs to the Unappropriated Surplus and/or reappropriate the same for other felt-need   PPAs.

We recommended that management:
Implement the Rice Retailing program and Potable Water Purification System in accordance with the Memorandum of Agreement for the beneficial use  of the identified proponents;
Otherwise, return the funds to the source agency so that it could be reprogrammed for other PPAs of the national government.

To avoid accumula-tion of unliquidated cash advances, we recommend that management instruct the Municipal Ac-countant to:

a) immediate settlement/liquidation of the outstanding cash advances for all concerned account-able officers pursuant to Section 89 of PD No. 1445 and COA Circular No. 97-002;
b) strictly mon-itor the liquidation of cash advances;
c) avoid granting additional cash advances unless the previous cash ad-vance given is first settled or proper accounting thereof is made pursuant to Section 89 of PD No. 1445;
d) initiate the filing of appropriate Administrative Proceedings for Gross Neglect of Duty to those who failed to render account of their accountabilities after demand or Simple Neglect of Duty to those who failed to liquidate their cash advances in full within the prescribed periods pursuant to CSC Memorandum Cir-cular No. 12, s. 2012;
e) exert more effort to locate the whereabouts of separated accountable officers and issue follow-up demand letters; 
f) analyze the composition of the Advances to Officers and Employees ac-count and reclassify in accordance with the Revised Chart of Accounts for LGU for fair presentation in the financial statement; and 
g) make ap-propriate adjustment to close the amount with negative balances and those comprising of small  amounts or fractions of centavo.

a) The LSB convene to thresh out their concerns and problems  that are preventing performance of their duties and responsibilities;

b) The LSB  prepare the Annual SEF Budget following the procedure set forth in the Joint Circular and furnish the Local Accountant, Local Treasurer and Local Budget  Officer  a  copy of the budget;

c) The Local Accountant prepare the quarterly and annual report on SEF Utilization  using the format prescribed in the Joint Circular; 

d) Adhere to the Circular on the allowable expenses chargeable to SEF.

Furthermore, we recommend that the Local Chief Executive stop the practice of allowing reimbursement. Instead, payments should be made by check. Cash Advance should be granted to a Special Disbursing Officer who is under the administrative supervision of the LGU, and not to employees of DepEd.
